<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="R2-017" project="SprkChat Platform Enhancement R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Real Web Search Implementation — Replace Mock with Bing API, Scope-Guided Search, Citation Generation</title>
    <status>pending</status>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, search</tags>
    <estimated-effort>medium</estimated-effort>
    <parallel-group>B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>BFF API code implementation — replaces mock WebSearchTools with real Bing API integration including scope-guided search and citation generation; ADR-015 and ADR-016 constraints apply</rigor-reason>
    <dependencies>[006]</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Replace the mock `WebSearchTools.cs` implementation (GitHub #232) with a real Bing Web Search API
    integration that produces scope-guided search results with numbered citations.

    **Architecture**:
    - The class signature and AI tool registration remain the same — callers do not change
    - Add a fallback: if Bing API key (`BingSearch:ApiKey`) is not configured in settings,
      log a Warning and fall back to mock results (graceful degradation)
    - Configuration: `BingSearch:ApiKey`, `BingSearch:Endpoint` (default to Bing v7 endpoint),
      `BingSearch:MaxResults` (default 10)

    **Scope-guided search** (FR-10):
    - Before executing the search, read `ChatHostContext.ScopeSearchGuidance` (the `sprk_searchGuidance`
      field from the active scope, populated by `AnalysisChatContextResolver`)
    - If search guidance is non-empty, prepend it to the search query as a site/domain directive:
      e.g., guidance "prioritize Westlaw and LexisNexis" → query becomes
      `"Westlaw OR LexisNexis {originalQuery}"` or instruction-style depending on Bing's best approach
    - If no guidance, execute the query verbatim

    **Citation generation**:
    - For each Bing result (up to `MaxResults`), create a `CitationContext` with:
      - `SourceUrl`: the result URL
      - `Title`: the result display name
      - `Snippet`: the result snippet text (truncated to 500 chars)
      - `ConfidenceScore`: based on Bing result rank (1st = 0.95, 2nd = 0.90, ..., 10th = 0.50)
      - `SourceType`: `"[External Source]"` (per ADR-015 — mark all web results clearly)
    - Return citations alongside the search result text

    **Result composition**:
    - Synthesize Bing results into a single AI-readable text block with inline `[N]` markers
    - The `WebSearchTools` method returns both the synthesized text AND the citations list
    - The AI model uses the synthesized text in its response; the citations list is sent to the
      client via SSE `citations` event (existing event type)

    **Rate limiting**: Bing API calls are bounded — max 2 concurrent search calls per user per ADR-016.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer with Azure AI and Minimal API expertise</role>

  <goal>
    `WebSearchTools.cs` uses real Bing Web Search API when configured, falls back gracefully to mock
    when not configured, prepends scope search guidance to queries, and returns `CitationContext` list
    alongside synthesized results. Legal research queries prioritize authoritative legal sources per scope
    guidance (FR-10).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="Project specification — FR-10 (scope-guided web search with citations), ADR-015 (external source marking)">projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="Project AI context — ChatHostContext, ADR constraints, scope guidance flow">projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="Existing mock WebSearchTools — class to replace while preserving interface">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Tools/WebSearchTools.cs</file>
    <file purpose="CitationContext model — existing model to populate">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/CitationContext.cs</file>
    <file purpose="Analysis scopes pattern — how scope search guidance flows to tools">../.claude/patterns/ai/analysis-scopes.md</file>
    <file purpose="AI architecture reference — tool registration and ChatHostContext flow">docs/architecture/ai-implementation-reference.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">MUST read scope search guidance from ChatHostContext (flowed through the pipeline) — MUST NOT query Dataverse directly from the tool implementation</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">MUST mark all web search results as `[External Source]` in the CitationContext.SourceType — MUST NOT present web results as internal Spaarke data</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-016">Bing API calls MUST be rate-limited; MUST bound concurrent calls to max 2 per user; MUST return graceful degradation (mock) if rate limit is hit, not an error</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-10">Search synthesis MUST return numbered inline citations; MUST be guided by `sprk_searchGuidance` from the active scope</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec MUST">MUST NOT log search query content or result snippets at any log level above Debug — search queries may contain sensitive case-related terms (ADR-015)</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Tools/WebSearchTools.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/CitationContext.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgent.cs</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ai/analysis-scopes.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/ai-implementation-reference.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-015-ai-data-governance.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-016-ai-rate-limits.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern>Bing Web Search v7 API: `GET https://api.bing.microsoft.com/v7.0/search?q={query}&amp;count={n}` with `Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key: {apiKey}` header — returns JSON with `webPages.value[]`</pattern>
      <pattern>Graceful API key check: `if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(_options.ApiKey)) { _logger.LogWarning("Bing API key not configured — using mock results"); return MockSearch(query); }`</pattern>
      <pattern>Scope guidance query prepend: if guidance contains domain/site directives, use Bing's `site:` operator for domain restriction; for general guidance prepend as a free-text qualifier</pattern>
      <pattern>Citation confidence by rank: position 1 → 0.95, position N → max(0.50, 0.95 - (N-1)*0.05) — linear decay from first to tenth result</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      WebSearchTools.cs was marked as a mock in GitHub issue #232 during R1 development. It returns
      placeholder results that the AI model uses to demonstrate the citation pattern, but it does not
      actually call any search API. R2 replaces this with real Bing Web Search API integration.

      The "scope-guided" aspect (FR-10) is important for legal workflows: a Legal Research scope
      might have `sprk_searchGuidance = "Prioritize authoritative legal databases: Westlaw, LexisNexis,
      court opinion repositories"`. This guidance, when prepended to the search query, produces more
      relevant results for legal professionals than a generic web search.

      Note from spec unresolved questions: Bing Web Search API has rate limits and the expected query
      volume is unknown. The ADR-016 bounded concurrency (max 2 concurrent) is the initial
      safeguard. Caching of search results (same query within a short window) may be added in a
      future iteration — do NOT add response caching in this task (per ADR-014 — cache only final
      outcomes, not intermediate search results used in streaming generation).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      Depends on Task R2-006 (Phase 1 deployment). Independent of all other Group B tasks — safe for
      parallel execution. The `ScopeSearchGuidance` in ChatHostContext is populated by R2-020
      (AnalysisChatContextResolver real implementation), but this task should gracefully handle the
      case where guidance is null or empty (treat as no guidance). Own file: `Tools/WebSearchTools.cs`
      only.
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Read the current `WebSearchTools.cs` mock to understand the tool method signatures, return types, and how ChatHostContext is accessed</step>
    <step order="1">Read `CitationContext.cs` to understand the model structure and what fields need to be populated</step>
    <step order="2">Read `.claude/patterns/ai/analysis-scopes.md` to understand how `ScopeSearchGuidance` flows through `ChatHostContext`</step>
    <step order="3">Add `BingSearchOptions` configuration model and register it (if adding a DI registration is needed, check ADR-010 budget; prefer static configuration read to avoid adding a new registration)</step>
    <step order="4">Implement `BingWebSearchClient` as a private inner class or a simple `HttpClient`-based method within `WebSearchTools` — do NOT create a separate DI-registered service</step>
    <step order="5">Implement API key check and mock fallback as the first step of the search method</step>
    <step order="6">Implement scope guidance query modification: read `chatHostContext.ScopeSearchGuidance`, apply query prepend/modification if non-empty</step>
    <step order="7">Implement Bing API call with `HttpClient`, parse response JSON, extract `webPages.value[]` results</step>
    <step order="8">Create `CitationContext` list from results with position-based confidence scores and `[External Source]` marker</step>
    <step order="9">Synthesize results into numbered text block: `[1] {title}: {snippet}\n[2]...`</step>
    <step order="10">Ensure rate limiting: add SemaphoreSlim with maxCount=2 as a static/singleton field to bound concurrent Bing calls</step>
    <step order="11">Run `dotnet build` and verify no errors</step>
    <step order="12">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task R2-017 status to completed (🔲 → ✅)</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>dotnet</tool>
    <tool>git</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <artifact type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Tools/WebSearchTools.cs — real Bing Web Search implementation with scope guidance, citation generation, and mock fallback</artifact>
    <artifact type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Options/BingSearchOptions.cs (or similar) — configuration model for Bing API key and endpoint</artifact>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">With Bing API key configured, a web search returns real Bing results (not mock placeholders)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Without Bing API key configured, the tool falls back to mock results with a Warning log (no exception thrown)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">With `ScopeSearchGuidance = "Westlaw LexisNexis"`, the actual Bing query includes these terms prepended (verify via Debug-level query logging)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Each search result produces a CitationContext with SourceType = "[External Source]"</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The first result has ConfidenceScore = 0.95; the 10th result has ConfidenceScore &lt;= 0.55</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No more than 2 concurrent Bing API calls are in-flight simultaneously (bounded by SemaphoreSlim or equivalent)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Search query text and result snippets do NOT appear in logs at Info or higher levels (ADR-015)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build` passes with no errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The Bing Web Search API v7 endpoint is `https://api.bing.microsoft.com/v7.0/search`. If the
    project is already using Azure AI Search (which it is), there may be an `HttpClient` factory
    configured. Register a named `HttpClient` for Bing in the DI setup ONLY if the project already
    uses `IHttpClientFactory` — do NOT add a new DI registration for a standalone HttpClient if
    it would push the count higher.

    Check `appsettings.json` and `appsettings.Development.json` for the existing configuration
    structure to decide where to add `BingSearch:ApiKey`. The key value in development should be
    in `config/local.json` (gitignored) per the security guidelines.

    From spec unresolved questions: search result caching is NOT in scope for R2. If the same
    user sends the same query twice, Bing is called twice. This is intentional — search results
    may change, and caching introduces freshness concerns that are deferred to a future iteration.
  </notes>

